Prediction_0.1: SELECT DIVIDE(SUM(CASE WHEN bond_type = '#' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100, COUNT(bond_id)) AS percent FROM molecule JOIN bond ON molecule.molecule_id = bond.molecule_id WHERE label = '+'
Prediction_0.5: SELECT DIVIDE(SUM(CASE WHEN bond_type = '#' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100, COUNT(bond_id)) as percent FROM molecule JOIN bond ON molecule.molecule_id = bond.molecule_id WHERE label = '+'
Prediction_1.0: SELECT ( CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN bond_type = '#' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS FLOAT) * 100 / COUNT(bond_id) ) AS percent FROM molecule JOIN bond ON molecule.molecule_id = bond.molecule_id WHERE molecule.label = '+'

Question: Which publisher created more superheroes: DC or Marvel Comics? Find the difference in the number of superheroes.
Gold: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN T2.publisher_name = 'DC Comics' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN T2.publisher_name = 'Marvel Comics' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM superhero AS T1 INNER JOIN publisher AS T2 ON T1.publisher_id = T2.id
Prediction_0.1: SELECT publisher.publisher_name, COUNT(superhero.id) AS superhero_count, SUBTRACT(SUM(CASE WHEN publisher.publisher_name = 'DC Comics' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), SUM(CASE WHEN publisher.publisher_name = 'Marvel Comics' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) AS difference FROM superhero JOIN publisher ON superhero.publisher_id = publisher.id WHERE publisher.publisher_name IN ('DC Comics', 'Marvel Comics') GROUP BY publisher.publisher_name
Prediction_0.5: SELECT publisher_name, COUNT(*) as superhero_count FROM superhero JOIN publisher ON superhero.publisher_id = publisher.id WHERE publisher_name IN ('DC Comics', 'Marvel Comics') GROUP BY publisher_name ORDER BY superhero_count DESC
Prediction_1.0: SELECT publisher_name, COUNT(superhero.id) AS hero_count FROM superhero JOIN publisher ON superhero.publisher_id = publisher.id WHERE publisher_name IN ('DC Comics', 'Marvel Comics') GROUP BY publisher_name ORDER BY hero_count DESC

Question: Which toxic element can be found in the molecule TR151?
Gold: SELECT DISTINCT T.element FROM atom AS T WHERE T.molecule_id = 'TR151'
Prediction_0.1: SELECT DISTINCT atom.element FROM atom JOIN molecule ON atom.molecule_id = molecule.molecule_id WHERE molecule.molecule_id = 'TR151' AND atom.element IN ('cl', 'f', 'br', 'i', 'pb', 'te', 'sn')
Prediction_0.5: SELECT element FROM atom WHERE molecule_id = 'TR151' AND element IN ('cl', 'f', 'br', 'i', 'pb', 'te', 'sn')
Prediction_1.0: SELECT element FROM atom JOIN molecule ON atom.molecule_id = molecule.molecule_id WHERE molecule.molecule_id = 'TR151' AND element IN ('cl', 's', 'br', 'f', 'i', 'sn', 'pb', 'te', 'ca')

Question: What was the difference in gas consumption between CZK-paying customers and EUR-paying customers in 2012?
Gold: SELECT SUM(IIF(T1.Currency = 'CZK', T2.Consumption, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T1.Currency = 'EUR', T2.Consumption, 0)) FROM customers AS T1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID WHERE SUBSTR(T2.Date, 1, 4) = '2012'
Prediction_0.1: SELECT (SELECT SUM(Consumption) FROM yearmonth JOIN customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID = customers.CustomerID WHERE customers.Currency = 'CZK' AND yearmonth.Date BETWEEN '201201' AND '201212') - (SELECT SUM(Consumption) FROM yearmonth JOIN customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID = customers.CustomerID WHERE customers.Currency = 'EUR' AND yearmonth.Date BETWEEN '201201' AND '201212') AS DifferenceInConsumption
Prediction_0.5: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN customers.Currency = 'CZK' THEN yearmonth.Consumption ELSE -yearmonth.Consumption END) AS Difference_in_Consumption FROM yearmonth JOIN customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID = customers.CustomerID WHERE customers.Currency IN ('CZK', 'EUR') AND yearmonth.Date BETWEEN '201201' AND '201212'
Prediction_1.0: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN customers.Currency = 'CZK' THEN yearmonth.Consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN customers.Currency = 'EUR' THEN yearmonth.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS DifferenceInConsumption FROM yearmonth JOIN customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID = customers.CustomerID WHERE SUBSTR(yearmonth.Date, 1, 4) = '2012'

Question: What is the anti Cardiolipin antibody concentration of the female patient with the highest uric acid level in the normal range?
Gold: SELECT T3.`aCL IgG`, T3.`aCL IgM`, T3.`aCL IgA` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F' AND T2.UA > 6.5 ORDER BY T2.UA DESC LIMIT 1
Prediction_0.1: SELECT aCL_IgG, aCL_IgM, aCL_IgA FROM Laboratory JOIN Patient ON Laboratory.ID = Patient.ID WHERE SEX = 'F' AND UA > 6.50 ORDER BY UA DESC LIMIT 1
Prediction_0.5: SELECT aCL_IgG, aCL_IgM, aCL_IgA FROM Patient JOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID JOIN Examination ON Patient.ID = Examination.ID WHERE SEX = 'F' ORDER BY UA DESC LIMIT 1
Prediction_1.0: SELECT aCL_IgG, aCL_IgM, aCL_IgA FROM Laboratory JOIN Patient ON Laboratory.ID = Patient.ID WHERE SEX = 'F' AND UA = (SELECT MAX(UA) FROM Laboratory WHERE UA <= 6.50)

Question: Please calculate the race completion percentage of Japanese drivers from 2007 to 2009.
Gold: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.time IS NOT NULL, 1, 0)) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T1.raceId) FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN drivers AS T3 on T1.driverId = T3.driverId WHERE T3.nationality = 'Japanese' AND T2.year BETWEEN 2007 AND 2009
Prediction_0.1: SELECT ( CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT results.raceId) FILTER (WHERE results.time IS NOT NULL) AS REAL) / CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT results.raceId) AS REAL) ) * 100 AS race_completion_percentage FROM results JOIN drivers ON results.driverId = drivers.driverId JOIN races ON results.raceId = races.raceId WHERE drivers.nationality = 'Japanese' AND races.year BETWEEN 2007 AND 2009
Prediction_0.5: SELECT (CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT results.driverId) AS FLOAT) / CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT drivers.driverId) AS FLOAT)) * 100 AS completion_percentage FROM results JOIN drivers ON results.driverId = drivers.driverId JOIN races ON results.raceId = races.raceId WHERE drivers.nationality = 'Japanese' AND races.year BETWEEN 2007 AND 2009 AND results.time IS NOT NULL
Prediction_1.0: SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT results.driverId) FILTER (WHERE results.time IS NOT NULL) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT results.driverId)) AS race_completion_percentage FROM results JOIN drivers ON results.driverId = drivers.driverId JOIN races ON results.raceId = races.raceId WHERE drivers.nationality = 'Japanese' AND races.year BETWEEN 2007 AND 2009

Question: What percentage of patients with a proteinuria level within the normal range have a uric acid level below the normal range?
Gold: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(ID) FROM Laboratory WHERE `U-PRO` > 0 AND `U-PRO` < 30
Prediction_0.1: WITH normal_proteinuria AS ( SELECT COUNT(*) AS count FROM Laboratory WHERE U_PRO > 0 AND U_PRO < 30 ), normal_uric_acid AS ( SELECT COUNT(*) AS count FROM Laboratory WHERE UA <= 6.5 ), normal_both AS ( SELECT COUNT(*) AS count FROM Laboratory WHERE U_PRO > 0 AND U_PRO < 30 AND UA <= 6.5 ) SELECT (CAST(normal_both.count AS REAL) / normal_proteinuria.count) * 100 AS percentage FROM normal_proteinuria, normal_both
Prediction_0.5: SELECT (COUNT(*) * 100.0) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Patient) AS percentage FROM Patient JOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID JOIN Examination ON Patient.ID = Examination.ID WHERE Laboratory.U-PRO > 0 AND Laboratory.U-PRO < 30 AND Laboratory.UA <= 6.5
Prediction_1.0: WITH normal_proteinuria AS ( SELECT COUNT(*) as total_patients FROM Laboratory WHERE U_PRO > 0 AND U_PRO < 30 ), below_normal_uric_acid AS ( SELECT COUNT(*) as patients_with_condition FROM Laboratory WHERE U_PRO > 0 AND U_PRO < 30 AND UA <= 6.5 ) SELECT (CAST(patients_with_condition AS REAL) / total_patients) * 100 as percentage FROM normal_proteinuria, below_normal_uric_acid

Question: What percentage of male patients who first presented to the hospital in 1981 were diagnosed with BEHCET?
Gold: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Diagnosis = 'BEHCET' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(ID) FROM Patient WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', `First Date`) = '1981' AND SEX = 'M'
Prediction_0.1: SELECT (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Diagnosis = 'BEHCET' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / COUNT(*)) * 100 AS Percentage FROM Patient WHERE SEX = 'M' AND YEAR(First_Date) = 1981
Prediction_0.5: SELECT (DIVIDE(SUM(CASE WHEN Diagnosis = 'BEHCET' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), COUNT(*)) * 100) AS Percentage FROM Patient WHERE SEX = 'M' AND YEAR(First_Date) = 1981
Prediction_1.0: SELECT CAST( COUNT(DISTINCT Patient.ID) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Patient.ID) FROM Patient WHERE YEAR(Patient.`First Date`) = '1981' AND Patient.SEX = 'M') AS REAL) AS Percentage FROM Patient JOIN Examination ON Patient.ID = Examination.ID WHERE Examination.Diagnosis = 'BEHCET' AND Patient.SEX = 'M' AND YEAR(Patient.`First Date`) = '1981'

Question: Among the patients who has a normal anti-scl70, how many of them are female and does not have any symptom?
Gold: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.SC170 = 'negative' OR T2.SC170 = '0') AND T1.SEX = 'F' AND T3.Symptoms IS NULL

Prediction_0.5: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Patient.ID) FROM Patient JOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID JOIN Examination ON Patient.ID = Examination.ID WHERE SC170 IN ('negative', '0') AND SEX = 'F' AND Symptoms IS NULL
Prediction_1.0: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Patient.ID) FROM Patient JOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID JOIN Examination ON Patient.ID = Examination.ID WHERE Laboratory.SC170 IN ('negative', '0') AND Patient.SEX = 'F' AND Examination.Symptoms IS NULL

Gold: SELECT T1.superhero_name, T2.publisher_name FROM superhero AS T1 INNER JOIN publisher AS T2 ON T1.publisher_id = T2.id WHERE T1.eye_colour_id = T1.hair_colour_id AND T1.eye_colour_id = T1.skin_colour_id

Prediction_0.5: SELECT superhero_name, publisher_name FROM superhero JOIN publisher ON superhero.publisher_id = publisher.id WHERE hair_colour_id = skin_colour_id AND hair_colour_id = eye_colour_id
